# Catalog Data Rules

- Treat `src/data/steering-data.js` as the canonical source for catalog entries and site links.
- Keep resource objects consistent: `name`, `path`, `summary`, `useItFor`, `shouldContain`, `usefulResources`, and `greatExamples`.
- Prefer official docs and strong public examples when adding links.
- Do not hand-maintain catalog guidance in `README.md`; run `npm run sync:readme` after changing source data.
- Keep `src/data/resources.ts` focused on shape validation and typed exports.
- Run `npm run build` after catalog or generator changes.
